---
# Auto-skills classifier configuration
# Copy to .claude/auto-skills.local.md in your project root (per-project)
# or to ~/.claude/auto-skills.local.md (global default)

enabled: true
sensitivity: normal    # low | normal | high
model: claude-haiku-4-5-20251001
effort: low
max_budget: ""         # max USD per classification call (empty = no limit)
debug_logger: false    # enable hook input debug logging

# Keywords for "low" sensitivity mode
low_keywords: "evaluate,investigate,implement,fix,debug,refactor,create,trace,analyze,review,critique,add,write"

# Environment variables for the claude -p subprocess (comma-separated KEY=VALUE)
subprocess_env: "CLAUDE_WORKTIME_SKIP_LOG=1"

# Category definitions — maps category name to trigger description and skill action.
# Each category is: name, description (for classifier prompt), action (injected as system-reminder).
# To add a custom skill: add a category entry and create the corresponding SKILL.md.
categories:
  - name: code-quality
    match: "User is asking to WRITE, EDIT, CREATE, or IMPLEMENT code — new features, bug fixes, refactoring, file creation. Confirming a proposal to implement counts. Also matches DESIGN CONSTRAINTS or CORRECTIONS directed at code being written."
    action: "Run /auto-skills:code-quality before writing code."
  - name: critical-thinking
    match: "User is asking to INVESTIGATE, DEBUG, TRACE, or ANALYZE something — find a bug, understand behavior, research a question, explain code."
    action: "Run /auto-skills:critical-thinking before proceeding."
  - name: critical-evaluation
    match: "User is asking to EVALUATE, COMPARE, CHOOSE, or DECIDE between options, or asking for an opinion on a design, approach, or tradeoff."
    action: "Run /auto-skills:critical-evaluation before responding."
  - name: skill-design
    match: "User is asking to WRITE, UPDATE, DESIGN, or REVIEW a skill, rule, checklist, or prompt template."
    action: "Run /auto-skills:skill-design before writing or modifying skills."
---

Optional markdown body — ignored by the classifier. Use for notes about your configuration.
